Checking of homogeneity of an equation (by comparing the SI base units of the left and right hand side terms of the equation) is not only a powerful way of establishing if an equation is reasonable, but it also provides hints for guessing the actual equation.

A physically correct equation must be homogeneous. However, a homogeneous equation need not be physically correct. Ultimately, the validity of an equation can only be verified through experiments.

