### Cyclic Process

A series of processes that eventually returns a system to its initial state is called a cyclic process. On the PV diagram on the right, the system starts from state \(1\), undergoes a process \(A\) to state \(2\) and goes back to state \(1\) via another process \(B\).

_Net Change in Internal Energy_

Since the internal energy depends only on the state (i.e. the position on a PV diagram), the overall change in internal energy for a cyclic process must be zero; i.e. \((\overline{\Delta U})_{net}=(\Delta U)_{A\to B}+(\Delta U)_{B\to A}~{}=~{}0\)

_Net Work Done on System_

Since work done on the system \(W\) is given by the area under the graph, it is easy to see that

