\[KE_{max}=hf-\phi\]

where \(\phi\) is the work function of the metal that is illuminated.

Lenard had not verified this relationship for different light frequencies, so Einstein offered this as an untested prediction of his postulates. Robert Millikan subsequently took up the challenge and measured the stopping potentials for various metals and validated this relationship.

