Since the total linear momentum is conserved, if the parent nucleus was initially at rest, **the daughter nucleus and the \(\alpha\)-particle must have momenta that are equal in magnitude and opposite in direction.** Since the \(\alpha\)-particle has a much smaller mass, it carries away most of the kinetic energy.

